name: variantinternalid
label: variantInternalId
description: A unique proper name or character sequence that identifies this particular variation. (NCIT:C164813 )

name: alternatebases
label: alternateBases
description: An allele that varies in it sequence from what is considered the reference or canonical sequence at that location. (GENO:0000002 )

name: referencebases
label: referenceBases
description: An attribute inhering in a feature that is designated to serve as a standard against which 'variant' versions of the same location are compared. (GENO:0000152 )

name: varianttype
label: variantType
description: An attribute describing a type of variation inhering in a sequence feature or collection. (GENO:0000773 )

name: position_start
label: position_start
description: The starting position of a sequence feature or interval. (GENO:0000894 )

name: position_end
label: position_end
description: The ending position of a sequence feature or interval. (GENO:0000895 )

name: position_assemblyid
label: position_assemblyId
description: The specific build of the human genome used as reference for this variant. (EDAM:data_2340 )

name: position_refseqid
label: position_refseqId
description: TODO unsure what is ment here - Refseq accession number of a transcript? (NCIT:C45335 )

name: identifiers_clinvarids
label: identifiers_clinVarIds
description: NCBI resource that aggregates information about genomic variation and its relationship to human health. (ENSGLOSSARY:0000242 )

name: identifiers_variantalternativeids
label: identifiers_variantAlternativeIds
description: A backup sequence of characters used to identify an entity. (NCIT:C90353 )

name: molecularattributes_aminoacidchanges
label: molecularAttributes_aminoacidChanges
description: A variation in the amino acid sequence of a specific gene product. (NCIT:C97928 )

name: molecularattributes_geneids
label: molecularAttributes_geneIds
description: A unique gene name within a specific repository, database, or collection. (NCIT:C48664 )

name: molecularattributes_genomicfeatures
label: molecularAttributes_genomicFeatures
description: A sequence feature (continuous extent of biological sequence) that is of genomic origin (i.e. carries sequence from the genome of a cell or organism) (GENO:0000481 )

name: molecularattributes_moleculareffects
label: molecularAttributes_molecularEffects
description: The effect that the variant has on each feature that it overlaps. A variant will have a consequence for each feature that it overlaps. (ENSGLOSSARY:0000134 )

name: variantleveldata_clinicalinterpretations
label: variantLevelData_clinicalInterpretations
description: The determination of the meaning of a clinical result. (NCIT:C125009 )

name: variantleveldata_phenotypiceffects
label: variantLevelData_phenotypicEffects
description: The likelihood of an entity to produce pathologic changes or disease. (NCIT:C168796 )
